<item>
            <title>[LU-9415] lfsck_load_one_trace_file() is too noisy</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9415</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Every time I mount an MDT I see the following on the console:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[941243.931146] LustreError: 23963:0:(lfsck_lib.c:2679:lfsck_load_one_trace_file()) lustre-MDT0000-osd: unlink lfsck sub trace file lfsck_namespace_00: rc = 0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;this &lt;tt&gt;CERROR()&lt;/tt&gt; should only be used in the error case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
